 DYNKINIndex
     Format:-DynkinI EXPR
      Modes:-REP
 Description:-Computes the total second order Dynkin index for the
             irreps in EXPR. See also the entry for the command  PROP.
             The normalisation is chosen to give the dynkin index a value
             of 1 for the fundamental irrep of the group.
    Example:-
             REP>
           ->gr e8
             Group is E(8)
  	     REP>
           ->dynkini 21^7
             2nd-dynkin = 1
             REP>
           ->dynkini 21
             2nd-dynkin = 25
             REP>
           ->dynkini 21^7 +2.21
             2nd-dynkin = 51
             REP>
